values:
So I have narrowed my options for college down to two places. It all depends on if I get into them. haha
Either TCC, which I have been accepted.. or Hunter College in New York City which I am still awaiting.
The end of the year is coming fast and I couldn't be more excited to get away from these immature girls
who party non stop. It gets really super old listening to their stories that I don't give two shits about.

And its even better when this person only talks to you when their "party" friends are pissing her off.
damn, why didn't i listen to my gut and stay far away from the bullshit. 
haaa whatever, college; i am ready for you.

o1. I'll respond with something random I like about you.
o2. I'll tell you what song/movie reminds me of you.
o3. I'll name something we should do together.
o4. I'll say something that only makes sense to you and me (or just me).
o5. I'll tell you my first/clearest memory of you.
o6. I'll leave you a quote that is somehow appropriate to you.
o7. I'll ask you something that I've always wondered about you.
o8. If I do this for you, you must post this on your journal. You MUST.
